verses.roman:
ihāṅ jagannāthera ratha-calana-samaya
gauḍa saba ratha ṭāne, āge nāhi yāya

synonyms: ihāṅ—outside the garden; jagannāthera—of Lord Jagannātha; ratha-calana-samaya—at the time of drawing the car; gauḍa—the workers named gauḍas who draw the car; saba—all; ratha ṭāne—pull the car; āge—forward; nāhi yāya—it does not go.
translation: Outside the garden, when it was time to pull Jagannātha's car, all the workers called gauḍas tried to pull it, but it would not move forward.
